Based on Section 6.1 of the Acquisition Agreement, the Ordinary Course of Business covenants are as follows:

The Company covenants that, from the date of this Agreement to the earlier of the Closing Date or the date on which the Company's shares cease to be listed on any stock exchange, the Company will carry on its business in an ordinary course of business, except as set forth in Section 6.1(b).

Section 6.1(b) specifically excludes the following actions from the ordinary course of business:

- (i) the sale, transfer, assignment, or other disposition of any of the Company's assets, except as contemplated by this Agreement;
- (ii) the incurrence of any Indebtedness;
- (iii) the payment of any dividends or distributions to Shareholders;
- (iv) the termination or material modification of any contract or agreement that is not in the ordinary course of business.

In other words, the Company is required to operate in the ordinary course of business, except for the specific exceptions mentioned in Section 6.1(b).
